The paper discusses the use of mutual information in classification neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given that the paper focuses on image classification and proposes a method for object localisation, it is most likely to be categorised under cs.CV. However, since the paper also discusses the theoretical implications of using mutual information in classification neural networks, it could also be categorised under cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
